00:17:19.415 --> 00:17:20.133
this is not the way;

333
00:17:20.599 --> 00:17:21.033
this is the way.

334
00:17:22.800 --> 00:17:24.733
In the same way, now, with Sahaja

335
00:17:24.733 --> 00:17:26.333
gravity, it should be taken to heart.

336
00:17:26.733 --> 00:17:30.735
It was why, yesterday, [I] spoke about sahaja dharma,

337
00:17:30.735 --> 00:17:31.833
that you love Me,

338
00:17:31.833 --> 00:17:32.466
I know.

339
00:17:32.666 --> 00:17:33.700
Too much love.

340
00:17:35.100 --> 00:17:36.266
And that you have faith in Me.

341
00:17:38.033 --> 00:17:39.110
That also I know.

342
00:17:39.810 --> 00:17:40.366
You

343
00:17:42.833 --> 00:17:45.433
feel like giving everything you have to Mother;

344
00:17:45.433 --> 00:17:46.533
that also I know.

345
00:17:48.200 --> 00:17:48.962
I know it all.

346
00:17:49.599 --> 00:17:50.966
That you love Me very much.

347
00:17:53.000 --> 00:17:55.633
But this devotion has to be brought into practice.

348
00:17:57.000 --> 00:17:58.000
And practice?

349
00:17:58.533 --> 00:17:59.171
What has Mother to do with it?

350
00:18:00.899 --> 00:18:02.766
You give something to Mother or not;

351
00:18:03.533 --> 00:18:04.934
it makes no difference to Mother.

352
00:18:07.366 --> 00:18:09.766
How much of a Sahaja Yogi are we becoming?

353
00:18:10.333 --> 00:18:12.666
How much of Sahaja dharma is growing within us?

354
00:18:13.166 --> 00:18:14.979
How much of the Sahaja attitude do we adopt in life?

355
00:18:14.979 --> 00:18:15.466
That should be observed.

356
00:18:18.466 --> 00:18:19.646
In the Sahaja buddhi (intellect), first of all, there

357
00:18:19.646 --> 00:18:21.066
should be ‘nirapekshita’ (no expectation, detachment).

358
00:18:22.200 --> 00:18:23.466
Nirapekshita means this –

359
00:18:24.833 --> 00:18:28.000
‘Sir, my house, my wife, my children.

360
00:18:29.100 --> 00:18:29.733
My ashram.

361
00:18:30.466 --> 00:18:31.733
Or my centre.

362
00:18:34.166 --> 00:18:36.099
‘Mother, you must come to My centre.’

363
00:18:36.333 --> 00:18:37.433
Before that, ‘Come to my house’;

364
00:18:37.433 --> 00:18:38.733
this used to happen very frequently.

365
00:18:38.833 --> 00:18:41.734
Now tell Me, if I go on visiting everyone’s homes,

366
00:18:41.734 --> 00:18:43.099
then what remains of Me?

367
00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:46.966
‘Alright, if not at home, please come to the centre.’

368
00:18:48.499 --> 00:18:50.766
Now going to the centre is also not so simple.

369
00:18:51.866 --> 00:18:54.666
‘Alright. If not the centre, can you at least come

370
00:18:54.666 --> 00:18:57.620
to the street corner over there?’

371
00:18:57.899 --> 00:19:00.899
[yogis laugh].

372
00:19:02.040 --> 00:19:02.400
Why?

373
00:19:04.340 --> 00:19:06.233
Because people see that,

374
00:19:07.500 --> 00:19:09.133
means everyone comes to know that

375
00:19:10.100 --> 00:19:11.760
– It is ‘I’. ‘I’ was the one who called Mataji and

376
00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:12.899
She came over to the street corner.

377
00:19:12.899 --> 00:19:14.499
This is the subtle thing.

378
00:19:16.166 --> 00:19:19.226
The subtlety here is – ‘I’ told Mother, and Mother

379
00:19:19.226 --> 00:19:22.166
came. Mother believes ‘me’ and so you should all

380
00:19:22.166 --> 00:19:23.366
believes me as well.

381
00:19:25.300 --> 00:19:26.999
That is its subtle thing.

382
00:19:32.633 --> 00:19:34.633
When this is understood –

383
00:19:36.700 --> 00:19:39.396
that I am there for Mother, my house is for Mother,

384
00:19:39.396 --> 00:19:40.899
everything is for Mother only

385
00:19:42.033 --> 00:19:43.766
– then Mother may or may not come.

386
00:19:45.433 --> 00:19:47.846
Does anyone invite themselves into their own house?

387
00:19:47.846 --> 00:19:50.866
Like, I am inviting Myself into My home.

388
00:19:51.733 --> 00:19:53.520
‘Its Your home’ – then why do you invite Me?

389
00:19:58.620 --> 00:20:01.266
And if all your money is Mine, then why do you give it?

390
00:20:03.333 --> 00:20:04.933
Speaking in

391
00:20:05.566 --> 00:20:07.199
everyday terms, if

392
00:20:08.500 --> 00:20:10.291
I say I am going to gift My kada (bangle) to Myself,

393
00:20:10.291 --> 00:20:11.610
you will say how is that even possible?

394
00:20:14.790 --> 00:20:16.978
Or if I invite Myself to My house [you will say],

395
00:20:16.978 --> 00:20:18.466
‘Did you fight with Your husband?’

396
00:20:22.300 --> 00:20:25.303
In the same way, in expressing sahaja, one must not

397
00:20:25.303 --> 00:20:28.307
think that this is my house, these are my children.

398
00:20:28.307 --> 00:20:31.600
They are all Mother’s. So wherever Mother is, it is Hers.

399
00:20:38.666 --> 00:20:40.066
And then I put you into confusion;

400
00:20:40.066 --> 00:20:41.166
that is another problem.

401
00:20:43.333 --> 00:20:44.998
And then they say, ‘Mother, we don’t know what

402
00:20:44.998 --> 00:20:46.699
happened. We went there with so much affection.’

403
00:20:46.699 --> 00:20:48.466
Alright. But bring it into behaviour.

404
00:20:48.466 --> 00:20:49.966
That should be understood.

405
00:20:50.533 --> 00:20:54.199
In Sahaja Yoga, the first thing is nirapekshita.

406
00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:58.266
The habit of being bound should start going away.

407
00:20:58.966 --> 00:21:00.633
For some it may be, ‘My wife;

408
00:21:02.466 --> 00:21:04.000
this [problem] of my wife should be made alright.’

409
00:21:04.633 --> 00:21:06.166
That should be detached immediately.

410
00:21:07.333 --> 00:21:09.833
One should be very attentive towards one’s own self.

411
00:21:11.066 --> 00:21:11.933
You may very well think,

412
00:21:13.766 --> 00:21:14.500
‘My son,

413
00:21:15.966 --> 00:21:17.066
he should go to Mother’.

414
00:21:17.766 --> 00:21:18.766
First, cut it out.

415
00:21:19.200 --> 00:21:20.699
Your son will be completely alright.

416
00:21:21.499 --> 00:21:23.500
Detachment is the solution to everything;

417
00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:25.100
you will be surprised.

418
00:21:30.460 --> 00:21:32.960
Yesterday someone had come. She was saying, ‘Mother,

419
00:21:32.960 --> 00:21:35.507
I had paralysis. I had this sickness, that sickness.’

420
00:21:35.507 --> 00:21:37.866
I could even remember her face. Had met only once.

421
00:21:38.633 --> 00:21:39.899
And she is now in first-class condition.

422
00:21:40.566 --> 00:21:43.099
She started saying, ‘I just used to sit with the photo.

423
00:21:43.866 --> 00:21:44.400
And

424
00:21:45.360 --> 00:21:46.633
my faith in that did the rest’.

425
00:21:46.800 --> 00:21:48.800
What happens is that when you take the

426
00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:50.300
photo and work hard with it,

427
00:21:51.666 --> 00:21:53.733
then you have to increase your faith.

428
00:21:55.066 --> 00:21:56.466
Because I am not in front [of you].

429
00:21:57.633 --> 00:22:00.564
You have to increase your faith, increase your depth.

430
00:22:00.564 --> 00:22:02.300
And when you reach the depth,

431
00:22:02.300 --> 00:22:03.766
that is when you get results.

432
00:22:06.866 --> 00:22:09.133
That is why, those who have got their self-realisation

433
00:22:09.133 --> 00:22:11.233
using the photo, they are sometimes much more

434
00:22:11.233 --> 00:22:13.333
[in quality] than those who are right now in front of Me.

435
00:22:14.266 --> 00:22:15.499
It is quite surprising.

436
00:22:17.233 --> 00:22:18.733
Or sometimes I see if Modi has

437
00:22:18.733 --> 00:22:19.833
given Self-realisation to someone -

438
00:22:20.466 --> 00:22:22.800
they do a lot to serve Me compared to

439
00:22:22.800 --> 00:22:25.266
those whom I gave Self-realisation directly.

440
00:22:25.800 --> 00:22:28.173
Because he has already drilled into them – this is

441
00:22:28.173 --> 00:22:30.499
Mother, you should understand it. She is Mahamaya.

442
00:22:31.566 --> 00:22:33.300
Do not come under Her illusion.

443
00:22:33.300 --> 00:22:34.866
Observe all protocols with Her.

444
00:22:36.133 --> 00:22:37.066
He explains it to them.

445
00:22:38.433 --> 00:22:40.566
But, if I give realisation to

446
00:22:40.566 --> 00:22:42.599
someone directly, they sit on My Head.

447
00:22:43.900 --> 00:22:44.733
Then, ‘I had come.

448
00:22:45.733 --> 00:22:47.410
I had especially come to meet You.’ Who told you to

449
00:22:47.410 --> 00:22:49.120
come especially? What kind of an especial person are

450
00:22:49.120 --> 00:22:49.830
you? Why did you come?

451
00:22:54.266 --> 00:22:55.599
So this ‘I’ness

452
00:22:56.666 --> 00:22:57.833
has to reduce.

453
00:22:58.233 --> 00:22:59.500
‘Me’, ‘mine’.

454
00:23:00.033 --> 00:23:01.799
That should be finished.

455
00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:06.166
Just like Kabirdas has said so beautifully,

456
00:23:06.533 --> 00:23:08.766
that when a goat roams about,

457
00:23:09.666 --> 00:23:10.499
alive,

458
00:23:10.833 --> 00:23:11.733
she keeps saying [bleats],

459
00:23:12.500 --> 00:23:14.433
‘mein, mein, mein’, ‘mein’.

460
00:23:15.466 --> 00:23:17.398
All this which we say, what he meant was this ‘mein’,

461
00:23:17.398 --> 00:23:19.257
‘mein’ [‘me’ is pronounced ‘mein’ in Hindi] – means

462
00:23:19.257 --> 00:23:21.233
we are all goats. ‘Mein, mein, mein, mein’.

463
00:23:23.300 --> 00:23:25.200
But when she loses her goat form,

464
00:23:25.200 --> 00:23:26.666
meaning when the goat dies.

465
00:23:27.366 --> 00:23:30.247
Her intestines are pulled out, washed, and dried.

466
00:23:30.247 --> 00:23:32.898
When they go on the road, pulling the strings

467
00:23:32.898 --> 00:23:35.952
[intestines made into a one-string instrument], then

468
00:23:35.952 --> 00:23:37.899
it says, ‘tuhi, tuhi, tuhi’ (only you).

469
00:23:38.800 --> 00:23:40.333
What a marvellous concept.

470
00:23:40.960 --> 00:23:43.838
He was a ‘julahe’ (weaver) and how he could see God

471
00:23:43.838 --> 00:23:45.333
Almighty in all his things.

472
00:23:46.500 --> 00:23:48.899
He would  say, ‘tuhi, tuhi, tuhi’.

473
00:23:49.333 --> 00:23:50.800
This idea will not enter our heads.

474
00:23:52.566 --> 00:23:55.202
So, when you become nirapeksha, then in everything

475
00:23:55.202 --> 00:23:57.837
you will see only Him, you will know only Him, you

476
00:23:57.837 --> 00:24:00.524
will understand only Him. And it will be surprising

477
00:24:00.524 --> 00:24:02.333
how, from all directions, it is all

478
00:24:04.200 --> 00:24:04.899
coming together.

479
00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:07.466
How this matter is coming together.

480
00:24:08.266 --> 00:24:10.766
Like, one girl arranged flowers for Me,

481
00:24:10.933 --> 00:24:11.866
on the ground.

482
00:24:12.900 --> 00:24:15.674
She said, ‘Mother, look, I have made Ganeshji. I just

483
00:24:15.674 --> 00:24:17.833
arranged it, how did Ganeshji get formed?’

484
00:24:18.366 --> 00:24:20.433
He guided your heart, your hand in

485
00:24:20.433 --> 00:24:22.299
the way needed to make Ganeshji.

486
00:24:22.933 --> 00:24:25.399
Which is very dear to Me.

487
00:24:29.966 --> 00:24:32.400
Just that was made, the one that is

488
00:24:32.400 --> 00:24:34.433
dearest [to Me], she made that.

489
00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:37.378
Because she had a surrendered heart, it [flower

490
00:24:37.378 --> 00:24:38.999
arrangement] became Ganeshji all on its own.

491
00:24:39.466 --> 00:24:41.160
The moment I saw it, I was in tears.

492
00:24:42.080 --> 00:24:44.166
‘How did you make My Shri Ganesh?’

493
00:24:47.166 --> 00:24:50.402
So we must keep the example of Shri Ganesh in front

494
00:24:50.402 --> 00:24:53.575
of us. Just like His devotion, so are His actions.

495
00:24:54.533 --> 00:24:56.533
One must follow the dharma of Shri Ganesha.

496
00:24:56.833 --> 00:24:58.800
For him, ‘tuhi, tuhi, tuhi’; besides

497
00:24:58.800 --> 00:25:00.366
that nothing else matters.

498
00:25:05.966 --> 00:25:07.899
He is ready on one leg.

499
00:25:10.800 --> 00:25:12.299
No need to say anything.

500
00:25:13.600 --> 00:25:15.323
No need to even desire.

501
00:25:15.323 --> 00:25:17.440
Someone just says something and He is gone after it,

502
00:25:17.440 --> 00:25:20.333
all the ganas running after Him and resolved it.

503
00:25:21.833 --> 00:25:24.154
And if you are useless, then He is also standing with

504
00:25:24.154 --> 00:25:26.346
the ‘parash’ (axe) in the other hand. Will fix it.

505
00:25:26.346 --> 00:25:27.999
Why did they go and say such a thing to Mother?

506
00:25:30.533 --> 00:25:33.978
Keeping [the ideal] of such Ganeshji in front of you,

507
00:25:33.978 --> 00:25:36.333
you should also get into Sahaja dharma.

508
00:25:37.500 --> 00:25:39.100
By coming into Sahaja dharma,

509
00:25:39.100 --> 00:25:40.666
you will experience such peace within.

510
00:25:42.100 --> 00:25:45.867
Because with Sahaja dharma all the insecurity

511
00:25:45.867 --> 00:25:49.168
that is inside, insecurities – they just are

512
00:25:49.168 --> 00:25:53.057
finished. We are playing in the lap of God Almighty;

513
00:25:53.057 --> 00:25:56.652
what do we care? Insecurity or anything else. So

514
00:25:56.652 --> 00:25:58.966
there is security, complete security.

515
00:26:03.466 --> 00:26:07.033
In a Sahaja person, that is a different type of

516
00:26:08.566 --> 00:26:13.202
attitude and we have to accept that attitude.

517
00:26:14.300 --> 00:26:17.535
Stubbornness goes away, speech changes, natures

518
00:26:17.535 --> 00:26:20.905
change. Diamonds have to be chiselled out. Sahaja

519
00:26:20.905 --> 00:26:24.544
Yogis are themselves diamonds – as the diamond of the

520
00:26:24.544 --> 00:26:28.184
Spirit within comes forward – the diamond’s different

521
00:26:28.184 --> 00:26:31.554
facets appear by themselves. And as I watch it, I

522
00:26:31.554 --> 00:26:35.126
keep feeling happier, ‘Splendid. How this diamond is

523
